LAGOS – Bukola Saraki, former Senate President and presidential hopeful on the platform of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) has said the level of insecurity and poverty in the country is unprecedented and so there must be power change from the All Progress  Congress (APC) to the PDP. The former Senate President who spoke on Monday when he visited the Lagos State delegates for the forthcoming convention and urged the delegates to vote for him because none of the aspirants under the PDP or the APC has the kind of capacity and experience that he has. -Advertisement- “We want a President that can unite the country, a President that cannot just sign memos but will know what is in the memo. We need a President that can unite Nigeria. A President that Nigerians will be proud of Details shortly.